metadata.dc:description: The position of the jugular bulb varies greatly. A high jugular bulb procident from the temporal bone is not uncommon. Most people with this anatomic variation remain asymptomatic. We report seven cases of high jugular bulb with clinical manifestations. The anatomy, clinical manifestations, diagnosis, and management are reviewed.
metadata.dc:title: Golfo yugular procidente. Revisión de siete casos.
[Protruding jugular bulb. A review of 7 cases].
